Parent: #133

**Complexity: Low** - Good for parallel work

## Task
Add `core help` command that displays help topics in the terminal.

## Commands

```bash
# List all help topics
core help

# Show specific topic
core help getting-started

# Show specific section
core help getting-started#installation

# Search help
core help --search "workspace"
core help -s "config"
```

## Implementation

```go
// internal/cmd/help/cmd.go

var helpCmd = &cobra.Command{
    Use:   "help [topic]",
    Short: "Display help documentation",
    Run:   runHelp,
}

var searchFlag string

func init() {
    helpCmd.Flags().StringVarP(&searchFlag, "search", "s", "", "Search help topics")
}

func runHelp(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) {
    catalog := help.DefaultCatalog()

    if searchFlag != "" {
        results := catalog.Search(searchFlag)
        // Display search results
        return
    }

    if len(args) == 0 {
        // List all topics
        topics := catalog.List()
        for _, t := range topics {
            fmt.Printf("  %s - %s\n", t.ID, t.Title)
        }
        return
    }

    // Show specific topic
    topic, err := catalog.Get(args[0])
    if err != nil {
        cli.Error("Topic not found: %s", args[0])
        return
    }

    // Render markdown to terminal
    renderTopic(topic)
}
```

## Terminal Rendering
- Use `github.com/charmbracelet/glamour` for markdown
- Or simple formatting with ANSI colors
- Pager support for long content (`less` style)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `core help` lists topics
- [ ] `core help <topic>` shows content
- [ ] `core help --search` finds topics
- [ ] Markdown rendered nicely in terminal
- [ ] Pager for long content
